ked files, which is good. I also see potential issues with several API functionalities, which need to be kept in mind for upcoming tasks.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Analyzing potential JAXB issues**\\\\n\\\\nI’m considering if `IDResolver.endDocument` gets called before the Patcher. Looking at how the JAXB unmarshaller might work, it seems like `endDocument` runs the patchers afterward, which is fine if `ended` is true after unmarshalling.\\\\n\\\\nI’m also thinking about the `SAXException` in overriding methods—might not be necessary if the superclass already handles it. There are some potential formatting issues related to namespace mappers and indentation that I need to further examine. Overall, I’ll have to weigh which elements I should keep for a robust solution.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Implemented comprehensive JAXB RI tests in:\\n\\n- `tests/src/com.sun.xml.bind/jaxb-impl/2.2.3-1/src/test/java/com_sun_xml_bind/jaxb_impl/Jaxb_implTest.java`\\n\\nCoverage added for:\\n\\n- JAXB marshal/unmarshal of annotated object graphs\\n- JAXB adapters, attributes, element wrappers, enums, and collections\\n- RI marshaller extension properties:\\n  - namespace prefix mapping\\n  - custom character escaping\\n  - indentation\\n- `JAXBRIContext`, `TypeReference`, and `Bridge`\\n- Custom `IDResolver` for `@XmlIDREF`\\n- `CycleRecoverable`\\n- Schema generation via `SchemaOutputResolver`\\n\\nNo reachability metadata or build files were modified, and I did not compile or run tests.\", \"textSignature\": \"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_045b521fb3dcf2f9016a26c9a0c3248193b1ee13f5472cedf0\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"oca/gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 321, \"output\": 830, \"cacheRead\": 57856, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 59007, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": 